<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/3161619-phoenix-blackdove"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1550491592i/3161619._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/3161619-phoenix-blackdove">Phoenix Blackdove</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes. I found it helpful both for the way Temple describes her personal ways of seeing the world, and for the references she lists. There&apos;s something b<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes. I found it helpful both for the way Temple describes her personal ways of seeing the world, and for the references she lists. There's something both revelatory and slightly creepy about reading, for the first time, an account by another person that so closely mirrors aspects of my life and thinking processes.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
