<div id="review_322746168" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/322746168" />
    <a title="Nikki" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5166784-nikki"><img alt="Nikki" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1338431988p2/5166784.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/322746168?book_show_action=true">May 02, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nikki" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nikki" href="/user/show/5166784-nikki">Nikki</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer322746168" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11711590738350159034">I was expecting more of a memoir, but this really ended up being Ms. Grandin&apos;s opinion on different aspects of autism with her own experiences only sprinkled in. It was difficult to get through the more technical aspects of the book and it was frustrating how often information was repeated. There were points that were interesting and I do feel like I have a better handle on autism in general, but that just wasn&apos;t what I was expecting when I decided to read this book. <br/><br/>If you are curious about aut</span>
  <span id="freeText11711590738350159034" style="display:none">I was expecting more of a memoir, but this really ended up being Ms. Grandin's opinion on different aspects of autism with her own experiences only sprinkled in. It was difficult to get through the more technical aspects of the book and it was frustrating how often information was repeated. There were points that were interesting and I do feel like I have a better handle on autism in general, but that just wasn't what I was expecting when I decided to read this book. <br /><br />If you are curious about autism and want to know Ms. Grandin's specific stance on issues related to autism then you should read this book. If you are looking for more of a memoir, this isn't what you want. </span>
